  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nMy intention was to send entire amount of an ERC20 token to another address.\r\n\r\nContext: ERC20 with 18 decimals\r\nEntire Amount in my wallet: all decimal was non-0:  the exact entire amount was using all 18 decimals\r\n\r\nISSUE 1: the displayed amount on Status was ceiled. So the displayed amount was grater then my actual amount (checked later with etherscan)\r\nSo when i manually set the amount it was accepted by the UI but then the transaction failed\r\n\r\nISSUE2: missing of \"MAX\" button which set the exact amount without having ti type it in my my self\r\n\r\nreplicated in ropsten:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15999009/74870719-7ac34100-535a-11ea-9f3d-2a128698a4f0.png)\r\n\r\nit seems that it is ceiled up to 14 decimals",
