    "body": "@hesterbruikman @andremedeiros This is very bad bug that needs to be fixed ASAP.\r\n\r\nThis causes transfers to fail, gas to be wasted, and is very hard to figure out why.\r\n\r\nIn case of SNT, this is what appears on etherscan: https://etherscan.io/tx/0xa6d220794018f90bbb6bb44ef4bbb74f541652ecb8b7482f17fdd67d51f606ba\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/tx/0xc4799419adf1619dd2c287e551bc79846d3ad1fea24aa4df380aecb155e9b415\r\n\r\nAfter manually setting the total value in the transfer value field, it goes correctly, see https://etherscan.io/tx/0x7aa74cab89bd600f46aaa4e22415d6e8f5b359489879c51f8c3cab77b875418b \r\n\r\nFor this transaction, the total balance was `1267.855876884165207048`, but when I press \"set max\" it filled `1267.8558768841653`\r\n\r\nFor me to be able to make it work I needed to manually load the balance in the smart contract, place the decimal in the correct place and paste it on the value field. ",
